📅 90‑Day SOC Analyst Roadmap

Phase 1 — Foundations (Days 1–30)

Build core skills in networking, OS internals, and cybersecurity fundamentals.

Networking (Week 1)

• TCP/IP, DNS, DHCP
• Subnetting & segmentation
• Packet analysis (Wireshark, Zeek)


Operating Systems (Week 2)

• Windows: AD, Event Logs, Group Policy
• Linux: syslog, permissions, processes
• PowerShell & Bash scripting


Cybersecurity Fundamentals (Week 3)

• CIA Triad
• Risk assessment
• MITRE ATT&CK, Kill Chain, Diamond Model


Log Analysis Basics (Week 4)

• Windows Event IDs
• Linux auth logs
• Parsing logs with scripts


---

Phase 2 — SOC Operations (Days 31–60)

Learn SIEM, EDR, NSM, and incident response workflows.

SIEM (Week 5)

• Splunk, ELK, Sentinel
• Log ingestion
• Correlation rules
• Dashboard building


Incident Response (Week 6)

• Alert triage
• Evidence collection
• Memory, disk, and network forensics


EDR / XDR (Week 7)

• CrowdStrike, SentinelOne, Defender
• Process trees
• Host isolation & remediation


Network Security Monitoring (Week 8)

• Zeek logs (conn, dns, http, ssl)
• PCAP analysis
• Beaconing & exfil detection


---

Phase 3 — Advanced Defense (Days 61–90)

Threat intelligence, vulnerability management, IAM, and advanced SOC skills.

Threat Intelligence (Week 9)

• OSINT workflows
• IOC enrichment
• ATT&CK mapping
• Threat actor profiling


Vulnerability Monitoring (Week 10)

• Nessus, Qualys
• Patch validation
• CIS benchmarks & drift detection


Identity & Access (Week 11)

• MFA, SSO, OAuth, SAML
• RBAC/ABAC
• Privilege escalation detection


Advanced SOC Skills (Week 12)

• Honeypots & deception
• Purple teaming
• Adversary emulation
• ATT&CK technique mapping


---

🔧 14 Hands‑On SOC Projects

Practical, real‑world projects to build confidence and skill.

1. Analyze a PCAP for suspicious traffic
2. Build a Splunk dashboard for authentication events
3. Write a correlation rule for brute‑force detection
4. Investigate a simulated malware infection
5. Perform memory forensics with Volatility
6. Parse Linux auth logs for anomalies
7. Create a PowerShell triage script
8. Enrich IOCs using VirusTotal + Shodan
9. Map a threat actor to MITRE ATT&CK
10. Run a Nessus scan and validate r
11. Detect privilege escalation in Azure AD logs
12. Deploy a honeypot and analyze interactions
13. Simulate a phishing campaign and analyze results
14. Conduct a purple team adversary simulation


Each project can be documented using your templates in /templates.

